metadata.name: Притяжение #70
metadata.description:
Inspired by Kazimir Malevich works, “Притяжение” features the connection between shapes, their positions and colours.
Although, as the work tries to develop further into a non-objective world, some real sceneries can still be associated with it.

metadata.name: Clew #562
metadata.description:
Thank you for adding me to your collection. Now that I’m a part of your tez fam, please open me in live view, enter ‘9’ or ‘10’, wait, press ‘P’, print me, put me on your wall, and enjoy.
__

Clew is a generative art collection designed for your wall.

When opening live view, you’ll be prompted to choose a render quality (1 for lowest; 10 for highest). The higher quality renders are for printing and zooming in to choose your own sub-composition or explore the details/depth. Higher quality images will naturally take longer to render but will be worth the wait. If you find a partial render particularly nice, you can press spacebar to pause (and unpause) the render. Save a PNG by pressing ‘P’ or a JPEG with ‘J’. Medium and high quality renders are optimized for Chrome desktop and may not function on other browsers or mobile devices.

The processing length varies considerably, depending on the assigned traits. Therefore, not all previews will reflect the final output.

created using p5js

Clew
abstractment, 2022

metadata.name: Migration #26
metadata.description:
"Migration" is a generative work with which I want to ease my worries about the irresponsibility of people towards the planet they live on.
If we migrate, I hope it will be for the purpose of exploring new areas and not because we have destroyed the planet we live on and are now forced to flee.

Created with 100% p5.js code and math.

Hi-res. options:

- press 'i' to save .png with resolution = 1000px x 1000px
- press 't' to save .png with resolution = 2000px x 2000px
- press 's' to save .png with resolution = 6000px x 6000px


@Mutart, July, 2022.

metadata.name: A long starry night #2
metadata.description:
This generative landscape is animated, some animations are very slow and take around 2 hours to loop.
This experience is best viewed fullscreen (click 'open' and go fullscreen) between FHD and QHD resolutions.

Press 'K' on the keyboard to go in the exploration mode. There you can drag the view with touch or mouse and orbit around stellar cluster.
Press 'K' again to embark on a travel following a celestial object.
Press 'SPACE' keyboard to take a screenshot (PNG) at current resolution.

attributes.name: In tribute to the science star

metadata.name: MONOLITH #110
metadata.description:
Very limited facts are known about these strange monolithic structures. Black, rectilinear, similar to obsidian stone but made of strange materials. According to legend, an ancient civilization of high intelligence, called the Explorers of Latent Space, distributed hundreds of monoliths throughout time and space in order to study the behavior of species in the infinite Universe.

Some say that it is the divine intelligence of God. Others say that, in spite of their objectual and material condition, the monoliths possess their own consciousness and an intelligence beyond the natural and artificial. Their purpose or objective, to this day, remains a mystery.

_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_

this work is done only with code, using threejs and p5js
it might be a bit slow on low-end devices, be patient

metadata.name: Flower Arrangement #202
metadata.description:
Flower arrangement made by code.

Possible features:
- Style: Natural, Oval, Triangular, Grassy
- Orientation: Square, Portrait, Landscape
- Palette: White, Cream, Tan, Pink, Green, Blue, Yellow, Orange
- Primary flower: Mix, Gerbera, Gerbera 2, Dahlia, Dahlia 2, Spiky, Unknown
- Primary color: Random, Light, Dark
- Secondary color: Random, Light, Dark
- Vase shape: Cylinder, Tumbler, Round, Curve
- Dish: true, false
- Table: true, false
- Texture: true, false

Live view options:
- Press "s" key: Saves the high resolution image (3300 x 3300 for square, 4200 x 3300 for portrait, 3300 x 4200 for landscape)

Depending on the device you run it on, it may take some time for the drawing to complete.
Best viewed in larger window size.
Made with p5js.

August 2022

objkt.name: Urban Building: Where Are We Going? #5

metadata.name: Urban Building: Where Are We Going? #5
metadata.description:
This is a building generation made by pure code.

Urbanization at the almost everywhere in the world has stepped into an accelerating phase in last century. Buildings bring magnificent achievements and represent the human power over nature. But, following these tall and crowd buildings one by one, where are we going?

In this work, I generate different types of building with a special viewpoint, which represent different concepts of states we are going to. Hope you enjoy these varieties and coincidences.

Variables:
- 4 modes
- 4 environments
- 3 orbs
- 3 building density
- 3 building structures

Please be patient with drawing process.

issuer.name: Urban Building: Where Are We Going?

metadata.name: color combinations #88
metadata.description:
the 'color combinations' series was developed as an exercise of combining colors from a single defined palette and the attempt to make all 15 selected colors being able to work within each other.

the constant pursuit for perfectionism made me design more than 200 tentatives of creating a perfect circle, and therefore the circle is the rarest output for the series.

i hope this series serves as a reference and inspire everyone out there.

2,340 possible combinations.
the closer the shape to the circle the rarer - ranging from 100% to 5%.
the bigger the shape the rarer - ranging from 30% to 20%.
beige and black colors are rarer - ranging from 100% to 5%

metadata.name: Sherwood #25
metadata.description:
In the forest, foggy, cloudy weather creates a mysterious, otherworldly atmosphere.

----

Controls:
s or [double click] - save
1 through 8 - set the pixel density for higher resolutions. Base is 2000x1000.
d - increase debug level (none, overlay, overlay + animated drawing)
D - decrease debug level
[plus] or [equal] - increase the edition of the mint (see a new location with the same features)
[minus] - decrease the edition, to a minimum of zero

Made with:
- p5js
- Simplex noise (hills, cleared/forested, grass height, tree size & separation)
- Poisson disk sampling (tree distribution)
